Reviewed lifecycle mapping treats CREATING as
provisioning, UPDATING as updating, ACTIVE and
INACTIVE as success, and DELETING as
terminating; FAILED is terminal and DELETED is
only a delete-confirmation target.
CreateKnowledgeBase returns a KnowledgeBase body
plus opc-work-request-id, while
UpdateKnowledgeBase and DeleteKnowledgeBase
return work-request headers without a resource
body. The runtime prefers the create response
identifier and otherwise recovers the
KnowledgeBase OCID from work-request resources
before rereading GetKnowledgeBase.
Pre-create reuse only runs when spec.displayName
is present and keeps exact compartmentId plus
displayName matching bounded to ACTIVE,
INACTIVE, CREATING, or UPDATING summaries.
Only displayName, description, indexConfig,
freeformTags, and definedTags reconcile in
place; compartmentId remains replacement-only
and ChangeKnowledgeBaseCompartment stays out of
scope for the published runtime.
Delete keeps the finalizer until the work
request is terminal and GetKnowledgeBase or
fallback ListKnowledgeBases confirms the
resource is gone.
end note
